Patch Set 5: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

The change looks good, so +1. I wonder whether it's worth to flag this patch as docImpact and explicitly specify in the documentation that when using --location + --size, the size will be verified *if* the remote location provides it. For example, an http location that doesn't return Content-Length will result in the --size parameter being ignored just as it is today.
